        <num>CC 3292</num>
        <heading>3292.  Mortgage of future property permitted in certain cases</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 3292.  Mortgage of future property permitted in certain cases
A special mortgage given over property the mortgagor does not own is established when the property is acquired by the mortgagor.  A general conventional mortgage is permitted only when expressly provided by law.</p>
        </content>
